1. Carto "Positron" (The "Apple Maps" look)

This is a light, grayscale map. It is perfect if you want your Purple and Grass Green markers to be the absolute stars of the show. It looks incredibly high-end and clean.

L.tileLayer('https://{s}.basemaps.cartocdn.com/light_all/{z}/{x}/{y}{r}.png', {
    attribution: '&copy; <a href="https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright">OSM</a> contributors &copy; <a href="https://carto.com/attributions">CARTO</a>'
}).addTo(map);

2. Carto "Dark Matter" (The "Tech" look)

If you want a dark mode map, this is the gold standard. The blue connecting lines will look like glowing neon against this background.

L.tileLayer('https://{s}.basemaps.cartocdn.com/dark_all/{z}/{x}/{y}{r}.png', {
    attribution: '&copy; <a href="https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright">OSM</a> contributors &copy; <a href="https://carto.com/attributions">CARTO</a>'
}).addTo(map);

3. Esri World Imagery (The Satellite look)

If you want to see actual buildings and grass, Esri provides a high-quality satellite tile layer for free.

L.tileLayer('https://server.arcgisonline.com/ArcGIS/rest/services/World_Imagery/MapServer/tile/{z}/{y}/{x}', {
    attribution: 'Tiles &copy; Esri &mdash; Source: Esri, i-cubed, USDA, USGS, AEX, GeoEye, Getmapping, Aerogrid, IGN, IGP, UPR-EGP, and the GIS User Community'
}).addTo(map);

Here are the specific L.tileLayer code blocks for the best free alternatives. You can simply copy and paste the one that fits your aesthetic best.
1. Carto Positron (Light & Minimal)

This is the "Apple Maps" style. It is the cleanest option and makes your purple and green markers stand out perfectly.
JavaScript

L.tileLayer('https://{s}.basemaps.cartocdn.com/light_all/{z}/{x}/{y}{r}.png', {
    attribution: '&copy; <a href="https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright">OSM</a> contributors &copy; <a href="https://carto.com/attributions">CARTO</a>'
}).addTo(map);

2. Carto Dark Matter (High-Tech Dark Mode)

If you want a modern, "command center" feel. The blue connecting lines will look like neon lights against this background.
JavaScript

L.tileLayer('https://{s}.basemaps.cartocdn.com/dark_all/{z}/{x}/{y}{r}.png', {
    attribution: '&copy; <a href="https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright">OSM</a> contributors &copy; <a href="https://carto.com/attributions">CARTO</a>'
}).addTo(map);

4. Carto Voyager (Soft & Colorful)

This is a middle groundâ€”it has more color than Positron (parks are green, water is soft blue) but is still much cleaner than standard OpenStreetMap.
JavaScript

L.tileLayer('https://{s}.basemaps.cartocdn.com/rastertiles/voyager/{z}/{x}/{y}{r}.png', {
    attribution: '&copy; <a href="https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright">OSM</a> contributors &copy; <a href="https://carto.com/attributions">CARTO</a>'
}).addTo(map);
